  "text": "As an alternative to the unbounded sigmoid activation function, we consider what statistical assumptions would be necessary to derive a version of the normalized exponential, or \"softmax\", activation function [CITATION_1] . This is the proper activation function to use in the case of a bounded number of categories greater than 2, so it is natural to expect it would generalize to the unbounded case. For this derivation we do not assume that one hidden layer activation pattern is sufficient to estimate a given category's probability, but instead make the much weaker assumption that the total set of all hidden patterns is sufficient. This alternative provides us with a normalization factor equal to",
